tool.name: CreateGRGFromArea

param.name: input_grg_area
param.dialogReference: Select an existing layer in the map, or use the tool to sketch an area on the map. The rotation of this input area determines the rotation of the output features.

param.name: cell_width
param.dialogReference: The width of each grid cell in the output features.

param.name: cell_height
param.dialogReference: The height of each grid cell in the output features.

param.name: cell_units
param.dialogReference:
The units of the Cell Width and Cell Height.

  • Meters

  • Feet

param.name: label_start_position
param.dialogReference:
The grid cell where the labeling will start from. The default is Upper-Left

  • Upper-Left

  • Lower-Left

  • Upper-Right

  • Lower-Right

param.name: label_type
param.dialogReference:
The labeling style for each grid cell. The default is Alpha-Numeric.

  • Alpha-Numeric: letter/number combination as A1, A2, A3, A4....X1, X2, X3...

  • Alpha-Alpha: letter/letter combination: AA, AB, AC, AD, ... XA, XB, XC...

  • Numeric: sequentially numbered 1, 2, 3, 4, .... 99, 100, 101...

param.name: output_grg_features
param.dialogReference: Specify the output grg features to be created.

tool.summary: Creates a Gridded Reference Graphic (GRG) over a specified area with a custom size. By default, the cells are labeled with a sequential alpha numeric scheme, starting in the lower left. The cells can also be labeled by a sequential alpha-alpha scheme or just numbers and the starting point can be specified as either the top left, bottom left, top right, or bottom right.
tool.usage:
• The output grid will expand to completely encompass the Input GRG Area

  • The rotation of Input GRG Area deteremines the rotation of the output grid.

  • The Grid (text) field in the Output GRG Features contains the cell labeling.

  • Output GRG Features are in a Web Mercator coordinate system.
